Add `rumpel grok` for the xAI Grok CLI

Integrate xAI's Grok CLI as a third agent alongside `rumpel claude`
and `rumpel codex`.  Grok is a terminal-native, Claude-Code-compatible
coding agent; it runs in-pod over a PTY session, so the launch path
mirrors `rumpel claude` while credential handling mirrors `rumpel
codex`.

- `rumpel grok <pod>` launches the grok TUI in a persistent screen
  session in the pod and attaches to it.  `--always-approve` is passed
  by default (the pod is the sandbox); disable via `--no-always-approve`
  or the `grok.alwaysApprove` config key.
- Auth is forwarded two ways: the host's `XAI_API_KEY` is injected into
  the session environment, and `~/.grok/auth.json` (from `grok login`)
  is copied into the pod when present.
- The Grok CLI is a pinned, statically-linked binary installed into the
  prepared image (and the devcontainer) per host architecture.
- Grok state (`~/.grok`) participates in fork/recreate state transfer.
- The LLM cache proxy gains an `xai` provider (api.x.ai, Bearer auth) so
  grok integration tests run deterministically offline.

Deferred: grok session-state notification hooks (the live
processing/waiting indicators that `rumpel claude`/`codex` surface).
